  correlationId,
});
```

## Best Practices

### Logging Guidelines

- **Be concise**: Include only necessary context
- **Use structured data**: Always use context objects, not string interpolation
- **Include correlation IDs**: Every log entry should have correlation ID
- **Log at appropriate levels**: Don't log debug info in production
- **Don't log PHI**: Redact sensitive data
- **Log state transitions**: Important state changes should be logged
- **Log errors with context**: Always include full error context

### Log Volume

- **Limit log entries**: Keep last 1000 entries per run
- **Rotate logs**: Clean up old logs periodically
- **Use log levels**: Filter by level to reduce noise

## Checklist

When implementing logging:

- [ ] Use `@chrome-ext/core-telemetry` logger
- [ ] Prefix logs with app tag
- [ ] Include correlation ID in all logs
- [ ] Include tabId, stepId, runId where applicable
- [ ] Store run logs in chrome.storage.session
- [ ] Implement live tail in sidepanel
- [ ] Implement log export functionality
- [ ] Redact PHI in logs
- [ ] Log state transitions
- [ ] Log errors with full context
- [ ] Track performance metrics
- [ ] Limit log volume (1000 entries per run)

